    "### Gravity Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Apply the gravity load according to the mass in the model:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T03:44:44.311885Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T03:44:44.311885Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T03:44:44.316392Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T03:44:44.316392Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T03:44:44.311885Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ops.timeSeries(\"Linear\", 1)\n",
    "ops.pattern(\"Plain\", 1, 1)\n",
    "_ = opst.pre.gen_grav_load(factor=-9810)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Analysis Parameters:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T03:44:44.317399Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T03:44:44.317399Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T03:44:44.325805Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T03:44:44.325805Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T03:44:44.317399Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ops.system(\"BandGeneral\")\n",
    "# Create the constraint handler, the transformation method\n",
    "ops.constraints(\"Transformation\")\n",
    "# Create the DOF numberer, the reverse Cuthill-McKee algorithm\n",
    "ops.numberer(\"RCM\")\n",
    "# Create the convergence test, the norm of the residual with a tolerance of\n",
    "# 1e-12 and a max number of iterations of 10\n",
    "ops.test(\"NormDispIncr\", 1.0e-12, 10, 3)\n",
    "# Create the solution algorithm, a Newton-Raphson algorithm\n",
    "ops.algorithm(\"Newton\")\n",
    "# Create the integration scheme, the LoadControl scheme using steps of 0.1\n",
    "ops.integrator(\"LoadControl\", 0.1)\n",
    "# Create the analysis object\n",
    "ops.analysis(\"Static\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

    "### Interacting with Pyvista"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since version 1.0.18, opstool provides a function ``get_nodal_responses_dataset`` that returns a pyvista [UnstructuredGrid](https://docs.pyvista.org/api/core/_autosummary/pyvista.unstructuredgrid#pyvista.UnstructuredGrid) so that you can take advantage of all the functionality on it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier New',monospace\"><span style=\"color: #cf6275; text-decoration-color: #cf6275; font-weight: bold\">OPSTOOL</span> <span style=\"color: #12e193; text-decoration-color: #12e193; font-weight: bold\">::</span>  Loading response data from <span style=\"color: #8e43e7; text-decoration-color: #8e43e7; font-weight: bold\">.opstool.output/RespStepData-</span><span style=\"color: #8e43e7; text-decoration-color: #8e43e7; font-weight: bold\">1.</span><span style=\"color: #8e43e7; text-decoration-color: #8e43e7; font-weight: bold\">nc</span> <span style=\"color: #808000; text-decoration-color: #808000\">...</span>\n",
       "</pre>\n"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "\u001b[1;38;2;207;98;117mOPSTOOL\u001b[0m \u001b[1;38;2;18;225;147m::\u001b[0m  Loading response data from \u001b[1;38;2;142;67;231m.opstool.output/RespStepData-\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;142;67;231m1.\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;142;67;231mnc\u001b[0m \u001b[33m...\u001b[0m\n"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import pyvista as pv\n",
    "\n",
    "grid = opsvis.get_nodal_responses_dataset(\n",
    "    odb_tag=1,\n",
    "    step=\"absMax\",\n",
    "    resp_type=\"disp\",\n",
    "    resp_dof=[\"UX\", \"UY\", \"UZ\"],\n",
    "    defo_scale=100,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The name of the scalar data to be activated will be the passed in ``resp_type``:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",

      "  Z Bounds:   -8.045e+03, 2.775e+04\n",
      "  N Arrays:   1\n",
      "disp\n"
     ]

   ],

    "print(grid)\n",
    "print(grid.active_scalars_name)"
   ]

    "You can call the plot method directly:"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "You can also use the filters provided by pyvista:\n",
